Trade Syndic quartermasters report that dust scavenger birds are harassing mule trains and tearing into unsecured cargo along the Dustward Verge. Convoy insurance claims have spiked, and two scheduled departures have been postponed pending threat reassessment. Thin the scavenger bird population until convoy marshals can certify the route as insurable again. The postmaster needs your kill tally to file with the Syndic Council's risk-adjustment office.
Scavenger bird pressure along the Dustward Verge has dropped below the threshold that triggers convoy insurance surcharges. Trade Syndic quartermasters have cleared the postponed departures, and mule train drivers report intact cargo for the first time in weeks. The postmaster has filed your tally with the Syndic Council and noted that your work saved the convoy compact more in avoided claims than the posted reward cost.
